                            <comment id="139778" author="pjones" created="Fri, 22 Jan 2016 19:13:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yang Sheng&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like this is an ongoing nuisance in testing. It looks like you had a debug patch under &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7118&quot; title=&quot;sanity-scrub: No sub tests failed in this test set&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7118&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7118&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and the thinking on the triage call was that this was related to this same issue. Is that the case? If so, are you able to run the test multiple times using test parameters so as to gather more information about what is happening here?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
